rComments: Great professor! Really cares about the subject matter, as well as her students. Has a deep well of knowledge on Russian history---brings up a lot of entertaining anecdotes from it! Provides good accommodations when needed.

Really straightforward classes. Easy to ask questions to and she'll try to answer if she can. The readings for the class were helpful and relevant to the focus of that day. Easy to approach outside of class, assignments aren't hard but make sure you keep up with them and their deadlines.
great prof! lots of fun little videos at the beginning of lecture
Professor Smith was a fun lecturer who sometimes goes off on tangents about background information. Just make sure you do the readings because multiple assignments require course readings.

Interesting and dense lectures, relevant and interesting readings. She is very nice herself, with interesting personal stories that only adds to the experience. Be prepared to come to class, you'll be at a huge disadvantage if you don't.
I wish there was a director's cut of her lectures. She always gets on these entertaining tangents, but has to cut herself short to finish the lecture on time.
An amazing lecturer, pretty easy-going and funny, with a generous grading scheme. Russian history would be awesome anyway, but she just makes it even better

Wonderfully spoken and enthusiastic. Tough marker. Terrible at conveying to the students what is important and what is not. Expects students to remember menial details from lectures and readings for the exam. Great Lectures, Terrible exam.
It's rather difficult to ascertain what's important and what isn't in her lectures. I love the material but not her presentation.
Obviously enthusiastic about the subject. Dismal at clarifying what she wants us to know.

She's an amazing prof! Incredibly enthusiastic and passionate about the material-- I was never bored at her lectures and actually wanted them to last longer!  She's also very stylish, and I love her voice! :)
one of the best history professors ever!!!she's very passionate and enthusiastic about the course, which engaged students. her lectures were very organized and easy to follow.

She is smart, approachable, decent, articulate, and really gorgeous. My complaints would be that she reads too many long quotes and gets too riled up while doing it. Also, her favourite word seems to be "problematic."
Great prof, highly recommended. And man is she hot.
she was very passionate about Russian history)) made it sound more interesting than it probably was =))

She's an okaay lecturer. While she's clearly passionate about Russian history, I don't think she's so passionate about lecturing. The way she structures her tutorials is pitiful. HOWEVER, she is very easy on the eyes. I love me a voluptuous woman.
Great prof! I have her this year for my russian history class and she's simply amazing! Best history prof so far! And definitly very very cute!!
Professor Smith is funny, and lectures so well you can remember how she said things while you study your notes. And it all sticks!!! (Plus, she's cute!)
Great professor. Funny, and makes somewhat uninteresting topics seem fun.
